 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 11:22:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=802.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: raid rules</span><hr size=1> IMO Hate is far more dangerous then Fear. Lots more roamers wandering around. Once Fear is broke that's pretty much it. Pull the FF and TT, Pull the two towers and boogey house move camp to tower etc. Fear is kinda a walk in the park the other day we cleared it with exception of the temple in 3 hours and I've yet to even hear of a hate raid coming close to that. In addition a total wipeout in Hate means 210pp for another rock, Fear you can just walk into. <p><img src="http://members.spinn.net/~paradise/tanise.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uthehitokiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thehitokiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 6:17:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=802.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: raid rules</span><hr size=1> I still don't understand why if you post that you are attending you don't get a spot. I can understand if I posted last and there is an abundance of your class. But if you amongst the first to post and one of the first in your class, i don't see why people who posted at the last minute will get picked over those who planned, reserved their time to attend, and etc. <br>
