~ thehitokiri<br>
56th Preserver of Clarus Somnium <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 7:00:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=802.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: raid rules</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
<br>
&quot;5. Don't ever be left alive with no clerics camped out after a train. In cases like that, being selfish is the worst thing you can do. Sacrifice yourself to give the clerics a few more seconds to get out. If you do so you may even end up with some rather cool screenshots hehe. Got a few of those myself, being left all alone in PoH with clerics camped out and a few dozen corpses lying around... and of course those 5 clerics of innoruuk beating on my sorry ass.&quot;  - Ulaian<br>
<br>
I will never forget one occasion like this. A long long time ago, on a Mithril Web raid, where some disastrous train by freak killed every cleric but me, and as the last alive cleric, I was told to camp. During those 30 seconds the sheer number of bodies thrown between advancing mobs and my seated self, only to be cut down, was horrendous. It was both touching and chilling to see ... and through their efforts, I camped out, and the raid was rezzed from there.<br>
<br>
As the cleric, I did nothing but watch them fall, knowing I had to make it out. The melee AND casters with their bravery did everything. It probably saved a 1-2 hour CR (at least).<br>
<br>
